parameters:
Amelia and Masamune are members of the Hero
Association, right?

You don't have to answer. Well, I can tell from
your reaction anyway.

Don't worry, I don't intend to report it to the
academy.
Rather, I am someone who monitors the academy.

Masamune, since you're a capable person, I'll let
you in on a secret.
I am a spy for the Empire.

(I thought you weren't just an ordinary student,
but I never expected that you were someone sent by
the Empire)

Does the Empire intend to oppose the Greatland
Kingdom...?

It's not something that grand. I'm just sending
information to my country.
There are people like that in every country.

And I didn't enter by falsifying my age either. I
enrolled through the proper method.
(How much information does this person have?)

Information doesn't flow out of the Magic Academy
easily.

That's why I have received a personal appointment
from His Majesty the Emperor and am gathering
information within the school.

I see... So that means they have also investigated
us.

Transfer students like you look suspicious from
the start. It's surprising that the academy
approved of you.

It seems like the Hero Association has been
working hard...

By the way, to have a personal appointment from
His Majesty the Emperor... He must be an amazing
person.

For me, His Majesty the Emperor is like a distant
figure in the clouds.

It's nothing special. The Kamono family has been
serving the Emperor for generations, that's all.

That's because I've been trained since I was
little.

Since we were little... it seems like Sayoko and
the others have had a tough time.

(Could it be that the dual personality is also
related to that...)

This conversation is over. Now that we know each
other's true identities, let's cooperate to a
certain extent.

I can't allow you to perform demon summoning or
research.

If the Greatland Kingdom falls into the hands of
demons, the next target might be the Imperial
Kingdom.
Hehe, do you really mean that?
...Well, honestly, I don't have any patriotism.

That's probably true. Most of the people at the
academy have enrolled because they had unpleasant
experiences.

As long as you don't become an enemy of the
Imperial Kingdom, I won't say anything.

Of course, anyone who acts against His Majesty the
Emperor will not be spared.

I'm not thinking about that. Neither am I the Hero
Association.

Well then, I'll go back to my room now. See you
tomorrow.
